modules.description: Performs a left fold over the characters of a string, applying a function to each character and its starting position. Works with strings and a custom folder type that processes characters and positions. Useful for parsing or transforming strings with position tracking, such as in lexers or text processors.

This module decodes Unicode characters from a byte stream using manual, channel, or string-based sources, managing decoding state and tracking byte positions. It supports incremental UTF-8 processing, allowing retrieval of decoded characters or malformed sequences as they occur. A child module provides position-aware string folding, enabling transformations that combine character data with their byte offsets, ideal for lexers or text processors. Together, they facilitate low-level byte-to-character decoding and high-level, position-sensitive string analysis.
